You know, messaging
me for help and all.

32
00:04:08,458 --> 00:04:12,166
I guess you're not going
to tell me what's wrong, huh.

33
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:16,500
What could be so terrible that
you don't want to go home?

34
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:19,333
Maybe you can tell me
later, if you want?

35
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:27,791
Going to answer?

36
00:04:33,416 --> 00:04:35,291
I see.

37
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:37,833
No. Leave him be for the moment.

38
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:41,291
Damn that Shu.

39
00:04:41,375 --> 00:04:43,708
Sorry to have made you wait.

40
00:04:43,791 --> 00:04:46,583
Hello again, Mr. Tsutsugami.
It's been a while.

41
00:04:46,666 --> 00:04:48,875
Please, call me Gai.

42
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:51,458
There's no need to be
so formal with each other.

43
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:56,416
Interesting reading. Truth be
told, I'd never have guessed

44
