that you were
his son, young man.

45
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,541
Whose son is he?

46
00:05:00,625 --> 00:05:03,875
Knowing that, I put
this question to you.

47
00:05:03,958 --> 00:05:07,166
What's your angle?
Why are you fighting?

48
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:09,750
What's worth risking
life and limb for?

49
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:14,291
It's all for a girl, of course.

50
00:05:14,375 --> 00:05:18,083
She's the reason I do this,
to hold her close.

51
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:20,000
Is that good enough for you?

52
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:30,708
Liberating Japan to impress some
girl, are you? I'll be damned.

53
00:05:32,583 --> 00:05:36,875
The stolen rock will arrive
in Haneda the day after next.

54
00:05:36,958 --> 00:05:39,333
From the looks of things,
Yan will send it overseas

55
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:42,125
at the first opportunity.

56
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:46,125
In every sense, that stone
belongs to the Japanese people.

57
00:05:46,208 --> 00:05:48,250
Wouldn't you agree, young man?

58
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:51,208
Yes, sir. We'll keep
it here, no matter what.

59
00:05:52,416 --> 00:05:56,125
Who would've thought,
this rock envied the world over?

60
00:05:56,208 --> 00:06:00,583
Would just fall into my hands
as though preordained.

61
00:06:00,666 --> 00:06:02,708
Men have been catapulted
into the White House

62
